empyrean — DUAL LICENSE
=======================

empyrean is distributed under two licenses, depending on the
component:

  * SOURCE CODE in this repository (Rust crates, C bindings, Python
    wrapper, CLI runner, build scripts, documentation) is licensed
    under the BSD 3-Clause License. The full text appears in
    Section A below and in `LICENSE-BSD`. You may freely use,
    modify, redistribute, and build derivative works subject to the
    BSD-3 terms (attribution + disclaimer).

  * BINARY DISTRIBUTIONS — the published Python wheel
    (`pip install empyrean`), the pre-compiled `libempyrean` shared
    library, and the `empyrean` command-line binary — are licensed
    under the proprietary Empyrean Binary License. The full text
    appears in Section B below and in `LICENSE-BINARY`. Binaries
    are free to install and use (including commercial use) but may
    not be redistributed, modified, reverse-engineered, decompiled,
    or disassembled.

Copyright (c) 2024-2026 Joachim Moeyens. All rights reserved.


